\section{1.8}

Consider the graph

\begin{figure}[h]
	\centering
	\includegraphics{graph1.jpg}
\end{figure}

Removing any edge on the left side will increase the min cut. 
Initially the left-side edges make up $\frac{1}{3}$ of the total amount of edges.
At every stage if the algorithm has not contracted any wrong edge, the probability of contracting a wrong edge is than at least $\frac{1}{3}$ 


